    "# Crossed vs Nested Random Effects Models in R\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates the differences between crossed and nested random effects models using R and the lme4 package.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Table of Contents\n",
    "1. [Introduction](#introduction)\n",
    "2. [Setup and Libraries](#setup-and-libraries)\n",
    "3. [Crossed Random Effects with lme4](#crossed-random-effects)\n",
    "4. [Nested Random Effects with lme4](#nested-random-effects)\n",
    "5. [Model Comparison and Diagnostics](#model-comparison)\n",
    "6. [Advanced Examples](#advanced-examples)\n",
    "7. [Conclusion](#conclusion)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Introduction\n",
    "\n",
    "R provides excellent tools for mixed-effects modeling, particularly through the `lme4` package. This notebook complements the Python examples by showing how to implement the same concepts using R's specialized syntax and functions.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key R Advantages:\n",
    "- Specialized syntax for specifying random effects\n",
    "- Comprehensive diagnostic tools\n",
    "- Extensive ecosystem for mixed models\n",
    "- Built-in support for complex variance structures"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load required libraries\n",
    "library(lme4)      # Mixed-effects models\n",
    "library(ggplot2)   # Plotting\n",
    "library(dplyr)     # Data manipulation\n",
    "library(tidyr)     # Data reshaping\n",
    "library(broom.mixed) # Tidy model outputs\n",
    "library(lattice)   # Additional plotting\n",
    "library(performance) # Model diagnostics\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set seed for reproducibility\n",
    "set.seed(42)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set plot theme\n",
    "theme_set(theme_minimal())\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Libraries loaded successfully!\")\n",
    "print(paste(\"lme4 version:\", packageVersion(\"lme4\")))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Crossed Random Effects\n",
    "\n",
    "### Example: Students, Teachers, and Items (Test Questions)\n",
    "\n",
    "In this example:\n",
    "- Students can be taught by multiple teachers\n",
    "- Teachers can teach multiple students  \n",
    "- The same test items are used across different student-teacher combinations"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Function to simulate crossed random effects data\n",
    "simulate_crossed_data <- function(n_students = 30, n_teachers = 8, n_items = 20, n_rep = 1) {\n",
    "  \n",
    "  # Create factor levels\n",
    "  students <- paste0(\"S\", sprintf(\"%02d\", 1:n_students))\n",
    "  teachers <- paste0(\"T\", sprintf(\"%02d\", 1:n_teachers))\n",
    "  items <- paste0(\"Item_\", sprintf(\"%02d\", 1:n_items))\n",
    "  \n",
    "  # Random effects (population parameters)\n",
    "  student_effects <- rnorm(n_students, 0, 1.2)\n",
    "  teacher_effects <- rnorm(n_teachers, 0, 0.8)\n",
    "  item_effects <- rnorm(n_items, 0, 0.5)\n",
    "  \n",
    "  # Create all combinations\n",
    "  data <- expand.grid(\n",
    "    student = factor(students),\n",
    "    teacher = factor(teachers),\n",
    "    item = factor(items),\n",
    "    rep = 1:n_rep\n",
    "  )\n",
    "  \n",
    "  # Add random effects\n",
    "  data$student_effect <- student_effects[as.numeric(data$student)]\n",
    "  data$teacher_effect <- teacher_effects[as.numeric(data$teacher)]\n",
    "  data$item_effect <- item_effects[as.numeric(data$item)]\n",
    "  \n",
    "  # Generate response (accuracy on 0-100 scale)\n",
    "  data$accuracy <- with(data, {\n",
    "    75 +  # Grand mean\n",
    "    student_effect + \n",
    "    teacher_effect + \n",
    "    item_effect + \n",
    "    rnorm(nrow(data), 0, 1.5)  # residual error\n",
    "  })\n",
    "  \n",
    "  # Ensure accuracy is within reasonable bounds\n",
    "  data$accuracy <- pmax(0, pmin(100, data$accuracy))\n",
    "  \n",
    "  return(data[, c(\"student\", \"teacher\", \"item\", \"accuracy\")])\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate crossed data\n",
    "crossed_data <- simulate_crossed_data(n_students = 20, n_teachers = 5, n_items = 10)\n",
    "\n",
    "cat(\"Crossed data dimensions:\", dim(crossed_data), \"\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\"Number of unique students:\", length(unique(crossed_data$student)), \"\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\"Number of unique teachers:\", length(unique(crossed_data$teacher)), \"\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\"Number of unique items:\", length(unique(crossed_data$item)), \"\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "head(crossed_data, 10)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Visualize the crossed structure\n",
    "library(gridExtra)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot 1: Heatmap of student-teacher combinations\n",
    "student_teacher_means <- crossed_data %>%\n",
    "  group_by(student, teacher) %>%\n",
    "  summarise(mean_accuracy = mean(accuracy), .groups = 'drop')\n",
    "\n",
    "p1 <- ggplot(student_teacher_means, aes(x = teacher, y = student, fill = mean_accuracy)) +\n",
    "  geom_tile() +\n",
    "  scale_fill_gradient(low = \"lightblue\", high = \"darkblue\") +\n",
    "  labs(title = \"Crossed Design: Student × Teacher Accuracy\",\n",
    "       x = \"Teacher\", y = \"Student\", fill = \"Mean\\nAccuracy\") +\n",
    "  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot 2: Distribution by teacher\n",
    "p2 <- ggplot(crossed_data, aes(x = teacher, y = accuracy, fill = teacher)) +\n",
    "  geom_boxplot(alpha = 0.7) +\n",
    "  labs(title = \"Accuracy Distribution by Teacher\",\n",
    "       x = \"Teacher\", y = \"Accuracy\") +\n",
    "  theme(legend.position = \"none\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot 3: Distribution by item (sample)\n",
    "item_sample <- crossed_data %>% filter(item %in% paste0(\"Item_\", sprintf(\"%02d\", 1:5)))\n",
    "p3 <- ggplot(item_sample, aes(x = item, y = accuracy, fill = item)) +\n",
    "  geom_boxplot(alpha = 0.7) +\n",
    "  labs(title = \"Accuracy Distribution by Item (Sample)\",\n",
    "       x = \"Item\", y = \"Accuracy\") +\n",
    "  theme(legend.position = \"none\", axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Combine plots\n",
    "grid.arrange(p1, p2, p3, ncol = 2, nrow = 2)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Crossed structure visualized: Each cell in the heatmap represents a unique student-teacher combination.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Fit crossed random effects model\n",
    "cat(\"Fitting Crossed Random Effects Model...\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\"Model formula: accuracy ~ 1 + (1|student) + (1|teacher) + (1|item)\\n\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fit the model\n",
    "crossed_model <- lmer(accuracy ~ 1 + (1|student) + (1|teacher) + (1|item), \n",
    "                     data = crossed_data)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Model summary\n",
    "summary(crossed_model)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Extract and visualize random effects\n",
    "library(sjPlot)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get random effects\n",
    "random_effects <- ranef(crossed_model)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot random effects\n",
    "p1 <- plot(random_effects$student, main = \"Student Random Effects\")\n",
    "p2 <- plot(random_effects$teacher, main = \"Teacher Random Effects\")\n",
    "p3 <- plot(random_effects$item, main = \"Item Random Effects\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Print variance components\n",
    "cat(\"\\nVariance Components (Crossed Model):\\n\")\n",
    "vc <- VarCorr(crossed_model)\n",
    "print(vc)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate ICCs\n",
    "var_components <- as.data.frame(vc)\n",
    "total_var <- sum(var_components$vcov)\n",
    "cat(\"\\nIntraclass Correlations:\\n\")\n",
    "for(i in 1:nrow(var_components)) {\n",
    "  icc <- var_components$vcov[i] / total_var\n",
    "  cat(paste(var_components$grp[i], \"ICC:\", round(icc, 3), \"\\n\"))\n",
    "}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Nested Random Effects\n",
    "\n",
    "### Example: Students Nested in Classrooms, Classrooms Nested in Schools\n",
    "\n",
    "This represents a clear hierarchical structure where:\n",
    "- Students belong to specific classrooms\n",
    "- Classrooms belong to specific schools\n",
    "- Students do not move between classrooms"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Function to simulate nested random effects data\n",
    "simulate_nested_data <- function(n_schools = 4, n_classes_per_school = 3, \n",
    "                                n_students_per_class = 8, n_obs_per_student = 2) {\n",
    "  \n",
    "  data <- data.frame()\n",
    "  student_id <- 1\n",
    "  class_id <- 1\n",
    "  \n",
    "  # School-level random effects\n",
    "  school_effects <- rnorm(n_schools, 0, 2.0)\n",
    "  \n",
    "  for (school in 1:n_schools) {\n",
    "    school_name <- paste0(\"School_\", sprintf(\"%02d\", school))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Classroom-level random effects within school\n",
    "    class_effects <- rnorm(n_classes_per_school, 0, 1.5)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for (class in 1:n_classes_per_school) {\n",
    "      class_name <- paste0(\"Class_\", sprintf(\"%02d\", class_id))\n",
    "      class_id <- class_id + 1\n",
    "      \n",
    "      # Student-level random effects within classroom\n",
    "      student_effects <- rnorm(n_students_per_class, 0, 1.0)\n",
    "      \n",
    "      for (student in 1:n_students_per_class) {\n",
    "        student_name <- paste0(\"Student_\", sprintf(\"%03d\", student_id))\n",
    "        student_id <- student_id + 1\n",
    "        \n",
    "        for (obs in 1:n_obs_per_student) {\n",
    "          score <- 70 +  # Grand mean\n",
    "                  school_effects[school] +\n",
    "                  class_effects[class] +\n",
    "                  student_effects[student] +\n",
    "                  rnorm(1, 0, 1.2)  # residual error\n",
    "          \n",
    "          data <- rbind(data, data.frame(\n",
    "            school = factor(school_name),\n",
    "            classroom = factor(class_name),\n",
    "            student = factor(student_name),\n",
    "            score = score,\n",
    "            observation = obs\n",
    "          ))\n",
    "        }\n",
    "      }\n",
    "    }\n",
    "  }\n",
    "  \n",
    "  return(data)\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate nested data\n",
    "nested_data <- simulate_nested_data(n_schools = 3, n_classes_per_school = 3, \n",
    "                                   n_students_per_class = 6, n_obs_per_student = 2)\n",
    "\n",
    "cat(\"Nested data dimensions:\", dim(nested_data), \"\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\"Number of schools:\", length(unique(nested_data$school)), \"\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\"Number of classrooms:\", length(unique(nested_data$classroom)), \"\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\"Number of students:\", length(unique(nested_data$student)), \"\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "head(nested_data, 10)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Visualize the nested structure\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot 1: School means\n",
    "school_means <- nested_data %>%\n",
    "  group_by(school) %>%\n",
    "  summarise(mean_score = mean(score), .groups = 'drop')\n",
    "\n",
    "p1 <- ggplot(school_means, aes(x = school, y = mean_score, fill = school)) +\n",
    "  geom_col(alpha = 0.7) +\n",
    "  labs(title = \"Mean Scores by School\", x = \"School\", y = \"Mean Score\") +\n",
    "  theme(legend.position = \"none\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot 2: Classroom means within schools\n",
    "class_means <- nested_data %>%\n",
    "  group_by(school, classroom) %>%\n",
    "  summarise(mean_score = mean(score), .groups = 'drop')\n",
    "\n",
    "p2 <- ggplot(class_means, aes(x = classroom, y = mean_score, fill = school)) +\n",
    "  geom_col(alpha = 0.7) +\n",
    "  labs(title = \"Classroom Means by School\", x = \"Classroom\", y = \"Mean Score\") +\n",
    "  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +\n",
    "  facet_wrap(~school, scales = \"free_x\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot 3: Nested boxplot\n",
    "p3 <- ggplot(nested_data, aes(x = school, y = score, fill = classroom)) +\n",
    "  geom_boxplot(alpha = 0.7) +\n",
    "  labs(title = \"Score Distribution: Schools and Classrooms\", \n",
    "       x = \"School\", y = \"Score\", fill = \"Classroom\") +\n",
    "  theme(legend.position = \"bottom\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot 4: Hierarchical structure visualization\n",
    "p4 <- ggplot(nested_data, aes(x = classroom, y = score)) +\n",
    "  geom_point(alpha = 0.6, position = position_jitter(width = 0.2)) +\n",
    "  stat_summary(fun = mean, geom = \"point\", color = \"red\", size = 3) +\n",
    "  stat_summary(fun = mean, geom = \"line\", color = \"red\", group = 1) +\n",
    "  labs(title = \"Individual Scores and Classroom Means\", \n",
    "       x = \"Classroom\", y = \"Score\") +\n",
    "  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +\n",
    "  facet_wrap(~school, scales = \"free_x\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Combine plots\n",
    "grid.arrange(p1, p2, ncol = 2)\n",
    "grid.arrange(p3, p4, ncol = 1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Fit nested random effects model\n",
    "cat(\"Fitting Nested Random Effects Model...\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\"Model formula: score ~ 1 + (1|school/classroom) + (1|school:classroom:student)\\n\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Method 1: Using nested notation\n",
    "nested_model1 <- lmer(score ~ 1 + (1|school/classroom), data = nested_data)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Method 2: Explicit nesting (equivalent to above)\n",
    "nested_model2 <- lmer(score ~ 1 + (1|school) + (1|school:classroom), data = nested_data)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Method 3: Including student level\n",
    "nested_model3 <- lmer(score ~ 1 + (1|school) + (1|school:classroom) + (1|school:classroom:student), \n",
    "                     data = nested_data)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Display summary of the most complete model\n",
    "summary(nested_model3)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Compare nested models\n",
    "cat(\"Model Comparison (Nested Models):\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\"================================\\n\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# AIC comparison\n",
    "aic_values <- c(\n",
    "  \"School only\" = AIC(nested_model1),\n",
    "  \"School + Classroom\" = AIC(nested_model2),\n",
    "  \"School + Classroom + Student\" = AIC(nested_model3)\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(aic_values)\n",
    "\n",
    "cat(\"\\nVariance Components (Full Nested Model):\\n\")\n",
    "vc_nested <- VarCorr(nested_model3)\n",
    "print(vc_nested)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot random effects for nested model\n",
    "re_nested <- ranef(nested_model3)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create plots for each level\n",
    "if(length(re_nested) > 0) {\n",
    "  for(i in 1:length(re_nested)) {\n",
    "    cat(\"\\nRandom effects for:\", names(re_nested)[i], \"\\n\")\n",
    "    print(head(re_nested[[i]]))\n",
    "  }\n",
    "}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Model Comparison and Diagnostics\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's compare the crossed and nested models and examine their diagnostic plots."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Model diagnostics for crossed model\n",
    "cat(\"CROSSED MODEL DIAGNOSTICS\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\"========================\\n\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Residual plots\n",
    "par(mfrow = c(2, 2))\n",
    "\n",
    "# 1. Residuals vs Fitted\n",
    "plot(fitted(crossed_model), residuals(crossed_model),\n",
    "     xlab = \"Fitted Values\", ylab = \"Residuals\",\n",
    "     main = \"Residuals vs Fitted (Crossed)\")\n",
    "abline(h = 0, col = \"red\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# 2. Q-Q plot\n",
    "qqnorm(residuals(crossed_model), main = \"Q-Q Plot (Crossed)\")\n",
    "qqline(residuals(crossed_model), col = \"red\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# 3. Scale-Location\n",
    "plot(fitted(crossed_model), sqrt(abs(residuals(crossed_model))),\n",
    "     xlab = \"Fitted Values\", ylab = \"√|Residuals|\",\n",
    "     main = \"Scale-Location (Crossed)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# 4. Random effects plot\n",
    "plot(ranef(crossed_model)$student[,1], \n",
    "     main = \"Student Random Effects (Crossed)\",\n",
    "     ylab = \"Random Effect\", xlab = \"Student\")\n",
    "abline(h = 0, col = \"red\")\n",
    "\n",
    "par(mfrow = c(1, 1))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Model diagnostics for nested model\n",
    "cat(\"NESTED MODEL DIAGNOSTICS\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\"=======================\\n\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Residual plots\n",
    "par(mfrow = c(2, 2))\n",
    "\n",
    "# 1. Residuals vs Fitted\n",
    "plot(fitted(nested_model3), residuals(nested_model3),\n",
    "     xlab = \"Fitted Values\", ylab = \"Residuals\",\n",
    "     main = \"Residuals vs Fitted (Nested)\")\n",
    "abline(h = 0, col = \"red\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# 2. Q-Q plot\n",
    "qqnorm(residuals(nested_model3), main = \"Q-Q Plot (Nested)\")\n",
    "qqline(residuals(nested_model3), col = \"red\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# 3. Scale-Location\n",
    "plot(fitted(nested_model3), sqrt(abs(residuals(nested_model3))),\n",
    "     xlab = \"Fitted Values\", ylab = \"√|Residuals|\",\n",
    "     main = \"Scale-Location (Nested)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# 4. School random effects\n",
    "if(\"school\" %in% names(ranef(nested_model3))) {\n",
    "  plot(ranef(nested_model3)$school[,1], \n",
    "       main = \"School Random Effects (Nested)\",\n",
    "       ylab = \"Random Effect\", xlab = \"School\")\n",
    "  abline(h = 0, col = \"red\")\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "par(mfrow = c(1, 1))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Comprehensive model comparison table\n",
    "library(broom.mixed)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Extract model information\n",
    "model_comparison <- data.frame(\n",
    "  Model = c(\"Crossed\", \"Nested\"),\n",
    "  Formula = c(\n",
    "    \"accuracy ~ 1 + (1|student) + (1|teacher) + (1|item)\",\n",
    "    \"score ~ 1 + (1|school) + (1|school:classroom) + (1|school:classroom:student)\"\n",
    "  ),\n",
    "  AIC = c(AIC(crossed_model), AIC(nested_model3)),\n",
    "  BIC = c(BIC(crossed_model), BIC(nested_model3)),\n",
    "  LogLik = c(logLik(crossed_model), logLik(nested_model3)),\n",
    "  N_obs = c(nobs(crossed_model), nobs(nested_model3)),\n",
    "  N_groups = c(\n",
    "    length(unique(crossed_data$student)) + length(unique(crossed_data$teacher)) + length(unique(crossed_data$item)),\n",
    "    length(unique(nested_data$school)) + length(unique(nested_data$classroom)) + length(unique(nested_data$student))\n",
    "  )\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(model_comparison)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Variance partition analysis\n",
    "cat(\"\\n\\nVARIANCE PARTITIONING\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\"===================\\n\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Crossed model variance components\n",
    "vc_crossed <- as.data.frame(VarCorr(crossed_model))\n",
    "total_var_crossed <- sum(vc_crossed$vcov)\n",
    "\n",
    "cat(\"Crossed Model Variance Partition:\\n\")\n",
    "for(i in 1:nrow(vc_crossed)) {\n",
    "  prop <- vc_crossed$vcov[i] / total_var_crossed\n",
    "  cat(sprintf(\"%s: %.3f (%.1f%%)\\n\", vc_crossed$grp[i], vc_crossed$vcov[i], prop*100))\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "cat(\"\\nNested Model Variance Partition:\\n\")\n",
    "vc_nested_df <- as.data.frame(VarCorr(nested_model3))\n",
    "total_var_nested <- sum(vc_nested_df$vcov)\n",
    "\n",
    "for(i in 1:nrow(vc_nested_df)) {\n",
    "  prop <- vc_nested_df$vcov[i] / total_var_nested\n",
    "  cat(sprintf(\"%s: %.3f (%.1f%%)\\n\", vc_nested_df$grp[i], vc_nested_df$vcov[i], prop*100))\n",
    "}"
   ]
